AI BulkSMS Shield – AI-Powered SMS Fraud Detection & Protection System

Problem Statement

Kenya and many African countries face increasing cases of SMS-based fraud, such as fake MPESA reversals, fake cash prize messages, fraudulent loans, and spam job offers. Millions of users—especially smartphone beginners—fall victim every year.
There is currently no tool that automatically scans SMS and alerts users when fraud is detected.

Proposed Solution

AI BulkSMS Shield is a mobile + web system that automatically:

Scans incoming SMS in real time

Uses Vertex AI to classify fraud, spam, and risky content

Uses Genkit to explain WHY the message is suspicious

Uses ADK to trigger alerts and workflows

Generates fraud logs and reports

Provides a dashboard for users and small businesses

The system works across Safaricom, Airtel, and Telkom.

Google Technologies Used
1. Vertex AI

Fraud message classifier

Fine-tuned text model for scam detection

Uses embeddings for similarity detection

Analyzes structure of MPESA messages

2. Genkit

Conversational reasoning agent

Provides plain-language explanations

Helps users understand risk levels

Powers support assistant

3. ADK (Application Development Kit)

Event triggers for HighRiskSMS

Notification workflows

Auto-report generation

Daily scanning routines

How the System Works

SMS is received → sent to Vertex AI

Vertex evaluates risks & flags fraud

Genkit explains findings

ADK triggers appropriate workflow (alert, log, notification)

Data is stored in Firebase

Dashboard visualizes fraud attempts

